\newlabel{fig:train_dynamics}{{2}{8}{Training dynamics of naive GRPO and GRPO with the DBB estimator (GRPO-DBB) on Qwen3-1.7B-Base (top) and Qwen3-8B-Base (bottom). GRPO-DBB achieves higher validation Acc@8 and training rewards, while maintaining longer responses with controlled entropy compared to GRPO, indicating more stable exploration during training}{figure.caption.4}{}}
\newlabel{fig:train_dynamics@cref}{{[figure][2][]2}{[1][7][]8}{}{}{}}
\newlabel{fig:mse_lambda}{{3}{8}{MSE as a function of the discount factor $\lambda $ and the number of rollouts $N$. The DBB estimator yields lower MSE than the point estimator across a wide range of $\lambda $, and it achieves lower MSE for rollout budgets up to $N=16$ when $\lambda =0.4$}{figure.caption.5}{}}
